val day                 = "2019-04-24" // begin date for the reads of the article that has been pushed. (also the date of the pushNotification) The data which is acquired is set 1 hour before this date (see variable "end")
val articleId           = "5452136" // the article that has been pushed
val daysBack            = 30 // get data from so many days back. At least one article from the tags of pushed articles has to be written in this period
val site = "nunl"
val filterUserTypes = Array("spns_device_secret")
val filterContentTypes = Array("article")
val tagMinViews = 0
val userMinViews = 0

val dateFormatter: DateTimeFormatter = DateTimeFormat.forPattern("yyyy-MM-dd").withZone(DateTimeZone.UTC)
val end = dateFormatter.parseDateTime(day).minusHours(1) //end date for acquiring data to train the models. Usually a day before the push notification will be send
val start = end.minusDays(daysBack)
val dBegin = dateFormatter.parseDateTime(day)
val dEnd = dateFormatter.parseDateTime(day).plusDays(1) //end date for the reads of the article that has been pushed

val s3BasePath: String = s"s3://sanoma-smbene-bigdata-team/dsnl/dev/recommendations/data/day_"+day+"_daysback_"+daysBack.toString
val s3pathData = s"$s3BasePath/app-articles-$site-userMinViews${userMinViews}-tagMinViews${tagMinViews}"

val nunlViews = SparkProfileDB
    .contentViews
    .read(site, start, end)(spark, Production)
    .filter(split($"useruniqueid", ":").getItem(0).isin(filterUserTypes:_*) && split($"contentUniqueId", ":").getItem(1).isin(filterContentTypes:_*))
    .cache()

// read article tags
val articlesNunl = SparkProfileDB
    .contentItems
    .read(site, ArticleType)(spark, Production)
    .selectExpr("uniqueid AS contentUniqueId", "tags")
    .filter(size($"tags") > lit(0))

// join together
val articlesWithTags = nunlViews
    .select("contentUniqueId")
    .distinct
    .join(articlesNunl, "contentUniqueId")
    .cache()

// users who have seen which tag and the count
val viewsWithTags = nunlViews
    .join(articlesWithTags, "contentUniqueId")
    .select($"userUniqueId", explode($"tags").alias("tag"))
    .groupBy("userUniqueId", "tag")
    .count

// filtering tags
val tagWithMinViews = viewsWithTags
    .groupBy("tag")
    .agg(count(lit(1)).alias("tagCount"))
    .filter($"tagCount" >= tagMinViews)
    
// filtering users
val userWithMinViews = viewsWithTags
    .join(tagWithMinViews, "tag")
    .groupBy("userUniqueId")
    .agg(count(lit(1)).alias("userCount"))
    .filter($"userCount" >= lit(userMinViews))
            
// filter combined  
val filteredData = viewsWithTags
    .join(userWithMinViews.select("userUniqueId"), "userUniqueId")
    .join(tagWithMinViews.select("tag"), "tag")

// String indexer for tags    
val ind1 = filteredData
    .select($"tag")
    .map(_.getString(0))
    .rdd
    .distinct
    .zipWithUniqueId
    .toDF("tag", "tagId")
    .cache

// String indexer for users
val ind2 = filteredData
    .select($"userUniqueId")
    .map(_.getString(0))
    .rdd
    .distinct
    .zipWithUniqueId
    .toDF("userUniqueId", "userId")
    .cache

// final dataset
val dataset = filteredData
            .join(ind1, "tag")
            .join(ind2, "userUniqueId")

// Most popular tags
val popTags = filteredData
    .dropDuplicates("userUniqueId")
    .groupBy("tag")
    .count
    .orderBy($"count".desc)

def getUserRecommendation(data: DataFrame, s3pathModel: String, threshold: Double, userUniqueId: String) = {
        // path of the item and user vectors which the model has created
        val s3pathItemFeatures = s3pathModel + "/itemFactors"
        val s3pathUserFeatures = s3pathModel + "/userFactors"
        
        // load the item and user vectors which the model has created
        val itemFeatures = spark.read.parquet(s3pathItemFeatures).cache()
        val userFeatures = spark.read.parquet(s3pathUserFeatures).cache()
        
        // udf: get the scores
        val udfGetScore = udf{ (itemFeatures: Seq[Float], userFeatures: Seq[Float]) => 
            val innerProduct = itemFeatures
                .zip(userFeatures)
                .map{ case (left, right) => left * right }
                .sum
    
            val itemLength = math.sqrt(itemFeatures.map(x => x * x).sum)
            val userLength = math.sqrt(userFeatures.map(x => x * x).sum)
            
            innerProduct// / (itemLength * userLength)
            }
        
        // udf: used for filtering if vector elements which are supposed to be 0, are about zero and therefore give scores which are not correct.
        val udfDist = udf{ features: Seq[Float] => math.sqrt( features.map(x => x * x).sum ) }
        
        // get the features of the user
        val userId = data
            .filter($"userUniqueId" === lit(userUniqueId))
            .select("userId")
            .collect
            .head
            .getAs[Long]("userId")
            .toInt

        val singleUser = userFeatures
            .filter($"id" === lit(userId))
            .selectExpr("features AS userFeatures")
        
        val tags = data.select("tag", "tagId").distinct()

        // We filter out items which have feature vectors with are near zero for all entries.
        // These items result in a very high score as the denominator gets very small.
        val recsSingleUser = itemFeatures
            .filter( udfDist($"features") >= 0.1 )
            .crossJoin(singleUser)
            .withColumn("score", udfGetScore($"features", $"userFeatures"))
            .orderBy($"score".desc)
            .selectExpr("id AS tagId", "score")
            .join(tags, "tagId")
            .select("tag", "score")
            .orderBy($"score".desc)
            .filter($"score" >= threshold)
        
        recsSingleUser
        }

import scala.util.Try
val threshold: Double = 0.6

s3Read.foreach{ s3Path =>
    val name = s3Path.split("/").reverse.take(1).mkString("/")
    val maxIter = name.split("-").take(2).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val rank = name.split("-").take(3).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val regParam = name.split("-").take(4).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val numUserBlocks = name.split("-").take(5).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val numItemBlocks = name.split("-").take(6).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val alpha = name.split("-").take(7).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    nunlContentItems.map { row =>
        val before = DateTime.now()
        val articleID = row.getString(0)
        if (articleID != "nunl:article:5451356") {
            Try{
                val tagsOfNotification =  row.getList[String](1).toSeq
                val readTags = nunlViews
                    .join(articlesWithTags, "contentUniqueId")
                    .select($"userUniqueId", explode($"tags").alias("tag"))
                    .filter($"tag".isin(tagsOfNotification:_*))
                    .dropDuplicates("userUniqueId")
                
                val prediction = getTagUsers(data = data, s3pathModel = s3Path, threshold = threshold, tags = tagsOfNotification)
                val joined = readTags.join(prediction, readTags("userUniqueId") === prediction("userUniqueId") , "inner")
                val joinedCount = joined.count
                val predCount = prediction.count
                val readCount = readTags.count
                val precision: Double = joinedCount*1.0 / predCount * 100.0
                val recall: Double =  joinedCount*1.0 / readCount * 100.0
                
                val after = DateTime.now()
                val dur = new Duration(before, after).getStandardSeconds().toString
                
                val res = Seq((articleID.toString, joinedCount.toString, predCount.toString, readCount.toString, rank.toString, regParam.toString, alpha.toString, maxIter.toString, numUserBlocks.toString, numItemBlocks.toString, precision.toString, recall.toString, dur.toString))
                val resDF = res.toDF("articleID", "joinedCount", "predCount", "readCount", "rank", "regParam", "alpha", "maxIter", "numUserBlocks", "numItemBlocks", "precision", "recall", "dur")
                resDF.coalesce(1).write.mode(SaveMode.Append).orc(s"s3://sanoma.dataservices.team/cda/dev/nunl/smart_push/model_training/result3")
                println(res)
                //res
            }
       }
   }
}

import scala.util.Try

def s3pathModel(maxIter: String, rank: String, regParam: String, numUserBlocks: String, numItemBlocks: String, alpha: String) : String = {
    s"""$s3BasePath/models/als-maxIter_${maxIter}-rank_${rank}-regParam_${regParam}-numUserBlocks_${numUserBlocks}-numItemBlocks_${numItemBlocks}-alpha_${alpha}"""
}

def s3pathDataset(maxIter: String, rank: String, regParam: String, numUserBlocks: String, numItemBlocks: String, alpha: String) : String = {
    s"""$s3BasePath/userTagScores/als-${maxIter}-${rank}-${regParam}-${numUserBlocks}-${numItemBlocks}-${alpha}"""
}

val output = s3Read.map{ s3Path =>
    val name = s3Path.split("/").reverse.take(1).mkString("/")
    val maxIter = name.split("-").take(2).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val rank = name.split("-").take(3).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val regParam = name.split("-").take(4).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val numUserBlocks = name.split("-").take(5).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val numItemBlocks = name.split("-").take(6).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    val alpha = name.split("-").take(7).mkString("-").split("-").reverse.take(1).mkString("-")
    
    val rankInt = rank.split("_")(1).toInt

    Try {
        //val s3PathModel = s3pathModel(maxIter.toString, rank.toString, regParam.toString, numUserBlocks.toString, numItemBlocks.toString, alpha.toString)
        //val newModel = model.createModel (data = data, implicitPrefs = implicitPrefs, nonNegative = nonNegative, maxIter = maxIter.toInt, 
        //rank =  rank.toInt, regParam = regParam, numUserBlocks = numUserBlocks, numItemBlocks = numItemBlocks, alpha = alpha )
        //model.saveModel (newModel, s3PathModel)
   
        val s3PathDataset = s3pathDataset(maxIter.toString, rank.toString, regParam.toString, numUserBlocks.toString, numItemBlocks.toString, alpha.toString)
        
        val s3pathItemFeatures = s3Path + "/itemFactors"
        val s3pathUserFeatures = s3Path + "/userFactors"
        
        // load the item and user vectors which the model has created
        val itemFeatures = spark.read.parquet(s3pathItemFeatures)
        val userFeatures = spark.read.parquet(s3pathUserFeatures)
        
        val userDenseFeatures = userFeatures
            .selectExpr("CAST(id as string) AS uniqueId", "features")
            .as[DenseFeatures]
        
        val itemDenseFeatures = itemFeatures
            .selectExpr("CAST(id as string) AS uniqueId", "features")
            .as[DenseFeatures]
        
        val dotProducts =  DotProductCalculator.computeAll(itemDenseFeatures, userDenseFeatures, rankInt, 200, Some(0.2))(spark)
            .selectExpr("uniqueIdLeft AS tag", "uniqueIdRight AS userUniqueId", "value as score")
        
        println("writing " + s3PathDataset)   
        
        dotProducts
            .write
            .orc(s3PathDataset)
            
        println("done")
        s3PathDataset
        }
}

import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window
val windowIndexX = Window.orderBy("tag")
val filteredDataTags = filteredData.withColumn("tagId", dense_rank.over(windowIndexX))

val windowIndexY = Window.orderBy("userUniqueId")
val filteredDataTagsUsers = filteredDataTags.withColumn("userId", dense_rank.over(windowIndexY))

val dataset = filteredDataTagsUsers.withColumn("rating", log(lit(1.0) + $"count"))

// // create userid indexer    
val userIdIndexer = new StringIndexer()
    .setInputCol("userUniqueId")
    .setOutputCol("userId")
    .setHandleInvalid("skip") //this has to be set to avoid an error, see also: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22446

// // create tag indexer
val tagIndexer = new StringIndexer()
    .setInputCol("tag")
    .setOutputCol("tagId")
    .setHandleInvalid("skip") //this has to be set to avoid an error, see also: https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22446

// // // create pipeline of indexers
val indexPipeline = new Pipeline()
    .setStages(Array(userIdIndexer, tagIndexer))

// // create indexer model
val indexModel = indexPipeline
    .fit(filteredData)

// apply indexer model and create rating column
indexModel
    .transform(filteredData)
    .withColumn("rating", log(lit(1.0) + $"count"))
}
